cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GR

The paper focuses on the use of deep learning models in computer vision, specifically in object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of synthetic data, which is a common topic in machine learning and deep learning research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the effects of having a limited amount of real data, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper uses simulation tools to create synthetic data, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics).
